    h1 MCP Server Setup

    p The Framework7 MCP server is available at:

    ```
      https://framework7.io/mcp
    ```

    h2 Cursor

    p Add to <code>.cursor/mcp.json</code> in your project:

    ```json
      {
        "mcpServers": {
          "framework7": {
            "url": "https://framework7.io/mcp"
          }
        }
      }
    ```

    h2 Claude Code

    p Add the MCP server using the CLI:

    ```shell
      claude mcp add --transport http framework7 https://framework7.io/mcp
    ```

    p You can verify it was added:

    ```shell
      claude mcp list
    ```

    p By default adds to local scope. Use <code>-s project</code> or <code>-s user</code> flags to change scope.

    h2 VS Code

    p Create <code>.vscode/mcp.json</code> in your project:

    ```json
      {
        "servers": {
          "framework7": {
            "type": "http",
            "url": "https://framework7.io/mcp"
          }
        }
      }
    ```

    p Or use the Command Palette: <b>MCP: Add Server</b> → HTTP → <code>framework7</code> → <code>https://framework7.io/mcp</code>

    h2 Codex (OpenAI)

    p Add via CLI:

    ```shell
      codex mcp add framework7 --url https://framework7.io/mcp
    ```

    p Or edit <code>~/.codex/config.toml</code>:

    ```toml
      [mcp_servers.framework7]
      url = "https://framework7.io/mcp"
    ```

    h2 OpenCode

    p Add to <code>opencode.jsonc</code>:

    ```json
      {
        "mcp": {
          "framework7": {
            "type": "remote",
            "url": "https://framework7.io/mcp",
            "enabled": true
          }
        }
      }
    ```

    h2 Other MCP Clients

    p Any MCP-compatible client can connect to the Framework7 MCP server using the Streamable HTTP transport. The endpoint is:

    ```
      https://framework7.io/mcp
    ```

    h2 Verify Connection

    p You can verify the server is running by checking the health endpoint:

    ```shell
      curl https://framework7.io/mcp/health
    ```

    p Or by sending an initialize request:

    ```shell
      curl -X POST https://framework7.io/mcp \
        -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
        -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"initialize","params":{"protocolVersion":"2024-11-05"}}'
    ```

